$\begin{align}
\text{Area of a rectangle} &= \text{width} \times \text{height}\\\\
&= 4\text{ meters} \times5 \text{ meters}\\\\
&= 20\text{ square meters}
\end{align}$

Now, Gia needs to find out how much paint she needs to cover her $20$ square meter wall with paint.

$\begin{align}
1\text{ liter} &= 10\text{ square meters}\\
{?}\text{ liters} &= 20\text{ square meters}
\end{align}$
